This paper deals with the design of a simultaneous information and power transfer scheme based on random medium access (RMA) for energy harvesting relay devices. The paper focuses on the optimization of the harvested power for an RMA scenario, which involves reliable symbol detection and prediction. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information processing capabilities. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.PE (Performance).
